title: Replies to supplementary questions raised by Finance Committee Members in examining the Estimates of Expenditure 2024-25
question_text: In addition to the Development Bureau and the Innovation, Technology and Industry Bureau mentioned in the reply, please elaborate, in table form, the details of other policy bureaux’s procurement of innovation and technology products and services of local enterprises.
reply_text: The Government has been actively introducing and applying innovation and technology (I&T) products and services from local start-ups. Based on the information provided by the Innovation, Technology and Industry Bureau, the Government has implemented measures such as the Public Sector Trial Scheme under the Innovation and Technology Fund, as well as the Smart Government Innovation Lab under the Office of the Government Chief Information Officer in recent years, with a view to playing a leading role. Information on the bureaux/departments (B/Ds) and the local I&T products and services involved in the above measures is set out at Annex. Session 6 FSTB(Tsy) - Page 10 Annex (1) Public Sector Trial Scheme The Public Sector Trial Scheme (PSTS) aims to provide funding to eligible local companies/organisations for producing prototypes/samples of their research and development (R&D) outcomes and conducting trials in the public sector (including government departments), so as to promote the realisation and commercialisation of R&D outcomes. Local I&T products/services under trial by B/Ds from January 2019 to end-December 2023 include – Session 6 FSTB(Tsy) - Page 11 Session 6 FSTB(Tsy) - Page 12 (2) Smart Government Innovation Lab Taking into account the business needs of B/Ds and the latest development of technologies, the Smart Government Innovation Lab assists B/Ds in arranging the activities such as technology matching, testing and proof-of-concept. Local I&T products/services that B/Ds have adopted in their current pilot projects from April 2019 to end-March 2024 are as follows – Session 6 FSTB(Tsy) - Page 13 Session 6 FSTB(Tsy) - Page 14 - End - Session 6 FSTB(Tsy) - Page 15
